      "id": "cc2e5f293ffc853884e6156ede842475a7f1b78a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2015-08-15 17:44:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI'm still not sure this is the correct approach. LFSCK prefetch the attributes from the targets and type of the target doesn't matter. when LFSCK finds a potential inconsistency, it acquires LDLM lock and re-fetch the attributes (IIRC). if you just disable those, then LFSCK's performance will suffer. let's discuss with Fan Yong first. probably we can invalidate the cache in osp_object_release() ?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
