      "date": "2015-08-24 17:44:03.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n\"LFSCK prefetch the attributes from the targets and type of the target doesn't matter. when LFSCK finds a potential inconsistency, it acquires LDLM lock and re-fetch the attributes (IIRC)\"\n\nCould you please tell me what cases LFSCK needs to fetch (validate) attributes from other MDTs?  Hmm, Just to be clear, I am not against to cache the attributes, but I thought it is pretty immature to use it in current stage without LDLM lock, plus there are memory corruption issue involved.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
