    {
      "id": "3dab927abdd6246527ad8fa83b59ba622e54244e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2015-08-27 02:20:59.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> I'm still not sure this is the correct approach. LFSCK prefetch the attributes from the targets and type of the target doesn't matter. when LFSCK finds a potential inconsistency, it acquires LDLM lock and re-fetch the attributes (IIRC). if you just disable those, then LFSCK's performance will suffer. let's discuss with Fan Yong first. probably we can invalidate the cache in osp_object_release() ?\n\nCurrently, only the cached OST-object's attr/xattr in OSP is valuable for LFSCK, because:\n\n1) The cached MDT-object's attr/xattr maybe changed by other on remote MDT, that will cause the local OSP cache to be invalid, then may misguide the local LFSCK.\n\n2) Compared with local MDT-object, remote MDT-object is relative rare case, cache remote MDT-object's attr/xattr in OSP will not bring significant performance benefit.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
